<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <p xml:id="Aink146-kilavi">
        varaivukaṭāvavum varaiyātoḻukukiṉṟuḻi nammai evvakai niṉaittār kollō eṉṟu aiyuṟṟirunta talaimakaḷ varaivu talaivantuḻit tōḻikkuc colliyatu. </p>    <p xml:lang="en">
          Spoken by the heroine, who was full of doubt, saying, ‘in which way did he think about us when he behaved without marrying, in order to marry [us]?’ to the confidante, when the marriage [finally] took place.
 </p>
 </div> 
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="Aink146">
<l>ekkar ñāḻa larumpumuti raviḻiṇar</l>
<l>naṟiya kamaḻun tuṟaivark</l>
<l>kiṉiya maṉṟaveṉ māmaik kaviṉē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
        <l>My dark beauty is pleasing indeed</l>
        <l>To the man from the ghat in which ripe, opening clusters of buds</l>
<l>Of the Ñāḻal tree in the dunes emit fragrance, so that they are fragrant. </l>     </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
